  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained money as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n2. European Union\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Comprehensive regulations across member states\n\n3. International standards\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Global guidelines for combating money laundering\n\nThese regulations typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Monitor and report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n- Conduct regular risk assessments\n\nFinancial institutions and businesses can face significant penalties for non-compliance with AML regulations.",
